'''基督教辨惑学'''（{{lang-en|'''Christian apologetics'''}}，这个词来源于[[希腊语|希腊语]]词汇{{lang|el|ἀπολογία}}，意为“以言语辩护”），或称'''基督教护教学'''，是[[基督教神学|基督教神学]]的一个分支领域，主要是为了展现基督教信仰的理性基础，针对批评而进行辩护，并揭露其他类型[[世界观|世界观]]中可察觉的缺陷<ref>{{cite_book |author=John M. Frame |title = Apologetics to the Glory of God |location=Phillipsburg |publisher=Presbyterian & Reformed |year=1994 |ISBN = 978-0875522432}}</ref>。基督教辨惑学具有多种形式。从使徒[[保罗|保罗]]开始以来的若干世纪里，相关人物包括[[俄利根|俄利根]]、[[希波的奥古斯丁|奥古斯丁]]等作家以及为现代教会团体做出贡献的[[G·K·切斯特顿|G·K·切斯特顿]]、[[C·S·刘易斯|C·S·刘易斯]]等。辨惑家以历史证据、哲学[[逻辑论证|逻辑论证]]、科学发现以及其他学科的论证为基础，站在基督教的立场上进行辨惑。术语“基督教辩论术”（{{lang|en|Christian polemics}}）则被用于表示[[护教士|护教士]]批判、攻击其他信仰系统的方式。<ref>Maijastina Kahlos, ''Debate and Dialogue: Christian and Pagan Cultures c. 360-430'' (Ashgate, 2007), pp. 7–9 ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=k3NH7dv1OfUC&dq=apologetics+%22christian+polemic%22&q=%22christian+polemic%22#v=snippet&q=%22christian%20polemic%22&f=false et passim]''; Ernestine van der Wall, "Ways of Polemicizing: The Power of Tradition in Christian Polemics," in ''Religious Polemics in Context. Papers Presented to the Second International Conference of the Leiden Institute for the Study of Religions'' (Van Gorcum, 2004), [http://books.google.com/books?id=plmPVHXb6PsC&pg=PA401&dq=%22christian+polemics%22&hl=en&ei=tae2TrmsE8LJgQer8YCHBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22christian%20polemics%22&f=false p. 401ff.]; Thomas E. Burman, ''Religious Polemic and the Intellectual History of the Mozarabs, c.1050-1200'' (Brill, 1994), [http://books.google.com/books?id=k1zQgoi3BwwC&dq=apologetics+%22christian+polemic%22&q=%22Christian+polemic%22+%22consisting+primarily+of+a+rather+strident+attack%22#v=snippet&q=%22Christian%20polemic%22%20%22consisting%20primarily%20of%20a%20rather%20strident%20attack%22&f=false p. 62] (on medieval Christian polemic against Islam); Jeremy Salt, "Imperial and the Christian Polemic," in ''Imperialism, Evangelism and the Ottoman Armenians, 1878–1896'' (Frank Cass, 1993) [http://books.google.com/books?id=Z59wTl4AuI4C&pg=PA9&dq=%22christian+polemic%22&hl=en&ei=46K2TpmiBMWCgAeB2vGXBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CF0Q6AEwCTgK#v=onepage&q=%22christian%20polemic%22&f=false p. 9ff.]; Alan F. Segal, "Judaism, Christianity, and Gnosticism," in ''Anti-Judaism in Early Christianity: Separation and Polemic'' (Canadian Corporation for Studies in Religion, 1986), [http://books.google.com/books?id=Xp6g6jde0lwC&pg=PA153&dq=%22christian+polemic%22&hl=en&ei=PaS2TvGpO-a10AH_nIXTBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CC8Q6AEwADge#v=onepage&q=%22christian%20polemic%22&f=false p. 153];Tim Hegedus,  ''Early Christianity and Ancient Astrology'' (Peter Lang, 2007), [http://books.google.com/books?id=USa7FTxP-okC&pg=PA23&dq=%22christian+polemic%22&hl=en&ei=daO2TtigKubh0QHx_JmqBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CEcQ6AEwBDgU#v=onepage&q=%22christian%20polemic%22&f=false p. 23]; Kathy L. Gaca, "Paul's Uncommon Declaration in Romans I:18–32 and Its Problematic Legacy for Pagan and Christian Relations," in ''Early Patristic Readings of Romans'' (T&T Clark, 2005), [http://books.google.com/books?id=gwCEWmb__UkC&pg=PA1&dq=%22christian+polemic%22&hl=en&ei=PaS2TvGpO-a10AH_nIXTBw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10&ved=0CGAQ6AEwCTge#v=onepage&q=%22christian%20polemic%22&f=false p. 1]; Arieh Kofsky, ''Eusebius of Caesarea against Paganism'' (Brill, 2000), [http://books.google.com/books?id=e9tCBO6TjYsC&dq=%22christian+polemic%22&q=%22christian+polemic+and+apologetic+literature%22#v=snippet&q=%22christian%20polemic%20and%20apologetic%20literature%22&f=false p. 4.]<!--this could go on and on, but "Christian polemic" does exist as a term of scholarly discourse --></ref>

== 圣经对辨惑学的推动 ==
在历史上，多篇《[[圣经|圣经]]》经文都推动了基督教辨惑学的形成与发展。

另外一篇常被基督教辨惑学引用的经文是《[[以赛亚书|以赛亚书]]》（{{CUV|以赛亚书|1|18}}）中涉及的上帝之约：“{{YHWH}}说：‘你们来，我们彼此辩论。’”<ref>{{cite book |last=Geisler |first=Norman L. |title=Christian Apologetics |year=1988 |publisher=Baker Academic |ISBN = 0801038227 |pages=11–12}}</ref><ref name="GroothuisCA" />

其他被用于基督教辨惑学基础的经文还包括《诗篇》第19篇，其开头是“诸天述说神的荣耀。穹苍传扬他的手段”（{{CUV|诗篇|19|1}}），还有《[[罗马书|罗马书]]》：“自从造天地以来，神的永能和神性是明明可知的，虽是眼不能见，但借着所造之物，就可以晓得，叫人无可推诿。”（{{CUV|罗马书|1|20}}）<ref>Owen Anderson, ''Reason and Worldviews: Warfield, Kuyper, Van Til and Plantinga on the Clarity of General Revelation and Function of Apologetics'', University Press of America, 2008, ISBN 0761840389, [http://books.google.com/books?id=LlrkFv4uvREC&pg=PA2 p. 2.]</ref>

== 历史 ==
早期的基督教[[护教士|辨惑家]]包括[[游斯丁|游斯丁]]、[[俄利根|俄利根]]和《[[丢格那妥书|丢格那妥书]]》的作者（姓名不详）<ref>[[Avery_Dulles|Avery Cardinal Dulles]], ''A History of Apologetics'', Ignatius Press, 2nd ed., 2005, ISBN 0898709334, [http://books.google.com/books?id=Xli4W2pSZpQC&pg=PA31 pp. 31–42.]</ref>。[[希波的奥古斯丁|希波的奥古斯丁]]也是[[教父_(基督教历史)|教父]]时期有显著影响力的辨惑家<ref>Dulles, [http://books.google.com/books?id=Xli4W2pSZpQC&pg=PA73 p. 73 ff.]</ref>。

[[托马斯·阿奎纳|托马斯·阿奎纳]]是天主教会一位有影响力的哲学家，他在其著作《[[神学大全|神学大全]]》里展示了其对上帝存在的五点论述<ref>{{cite web |title =Saint Thomas Aquinas (1225-1274), "The Five Ways" |publisher =Texas A&M University Department of Philosophy |url =http://www-phil.tamu.edu/~gary/intro/paper.aquinas.html |accessdate =2007-11-20 |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20071023014109/http://www-phil.tamu.edu/~gary/intro/paper.aquinas.html |archivedate =2007-10-23 |deadurl =yes }}</ref>。托马斯的另一作品《[[哲学大全|哲学大全]]》也是其主要的辨惑学著作<ref>Dulles, [http://books.google.com/books?id=Xli4W2pSZpQC&pg=PA120 p. 120.]</ref><ref>L. Russ Bush, ''Classical Readings in Christian Apologetics, A.D. 100-1800, Parts 100-1800'', Zondervan, 1983, ISBN 031045641X, [http://books.google.com.au/books?id=bKSm9HewJ1cC&pg=PA275 p. 275 ff.] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com.au/books?id=bKSm9HewJ1cC&pg=PA275 |date=20120723074846 }}</ref>。

法国[[宗教哲学|宗教哲学]]家（同时也是数学家、物理学家）[[布莱兹·帕斯卡|布莱兹·帕斯卡]]在其《思想录》（{{lang|fr|''Pensées''}}）概述了一种辨惑学的途径：“人类轻视宗教。他们憎恨并害怕它，这是事实。为了治疗这些人，我们必须先显示宗教与理智并非背道而驰，反而它是可敬的，激发对宗教的尊敬；然后我们必须使它值得被爱，让人们盼望其是实实在在的；最终，我们必须证明宗教是实实在在的。”<ref>[[Blaise_Pascal|Blaise Pascal]], ''Pensées'', [http://www.ccel.org/ccel/pascal/pensees.iv.html 187] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ccel.org/ccel/pascal/pensees.iv.html |date=20120103202033 }}.</ref><ref name="GroothuisCA">[[Douglas_Groothuis|Douglas Groothuis]], ''Christian Apologetics: A Comprehensive Case for Biblical Faith'', InterVarsity Press, 2011, ISBN 0830839356, [http://books.google.com/books?id=rQ_SdH1PWyMC&pg=PA25 pp. 25–31.]</ref>

=== 辨惑学的现状 ===
直到今天，基督教辨惑学还在以多种形式继续发展。[[罗马天主教会|罗马天主教会]]的[[G·K·切斯特顿|G·K·切斯特顿]]<ref name="everMan">{{cite book |last=Chesterton |first=G.K.|title = The Everlasting Man |year=2008 |publisher=Wilder Publications |ISBN = 160459246X |page = 180 |url = http://www.amazon.com/Everlasting-Man-Gilbert-K-Chesterton/dp/160459246X/ref=pd_sim_b_2}}</ref>、罗纳德·诺克斯（{{lang|en|Ronald Knox}}）、卡尔·基廷（{{lang|en|Karl Keating}}）、[[圣公会|圣公会]]的[[C·S·刘易斯|C·S·刘易斯]]（现在的“刘易斯三难窘境”（{{lang|en|Lewis's trilemma}}）就是由他普及的）<ref>Lewis, C.S., ''[[Mere_Christianity|Mere Christianity]]'', London: Collins, 1952, pp. 54-56. (In all editions, this is Bk. II, Ch. 3, "The Shocking Alternative.") Note: G. K. Chesterton used a similar argument about someone else in his ''The Napoleon of Notting Hill'' (1904): "He may be God. He may be the Devil. But we think it more likely as a matter of human probability that he is mad." See Cecil Chesterton, ''G. K. Chesterton: A Criticism'' (Seattle: Inklng, 2007), 26.</ref>、[[福音派|福音派]]的诺曼·盖斯勒（{{lang|en|Norman Geisler}}）、路德宗（即[[信义宗|信义宗]]）的约翰·瓦里克·蒙哥马利（{{lang|en|John Warwick Montgomery}}）和[[长老宗|长老会]]的弗朗西斯·谢弗（{{lang|en|Francis Schaeffer}}）都是20世纪最为知名的基督教辨惑家。此外，戈登·克拉克（{{lang|en|Gordon Clark}}）和科尼利厄斯·凡·蒂尔（{{lang|en|Cornelius Van Til}}）则开创了被称为“[[前提主义|前提主义]]”（{{lang|en|presuppositionalism}}）的哲学新学派，这一学说在[[加尔文主义|加尔文主义]]圈内比较流行。其他较为知名的辨惑学学者包括约什·麦克道威尔（{{lang|en|Josh McDowell}}）、拉维·扎克莱亚斯（{{lang|en|Ravi Zacharias}}）、休·罗斯（{{lang|en|Hugh Ross}}）、李·斯特罗贝尔（{{lang|en|Strobel}}）、雨果·安东尼·梅内尔（{{lang|en|Hugo Anthony Meynell}}）、提摩西·J·凯勒（{{lang|en|Timothy J. Keller}}）、阿尔文·普朗廷葛（{{lang|en|Alvin Plantinga}}）、威廉·莱恩·克雷格（{{lang|en|William Lane Craig}}）和皮特·克里夫特（{{lang|en|Peter Kreeft}}）。

== 种类 ==
基督教辨惑学有多种风格，并具有不同的思想流派。主要的类型包括：历史和律法辨惑、预先假定辨惑、哲学辨惑、预言辨惑、教条辨惑、圣经辨惑、道德辨惑以及科学辨惑。下面将介绍概括性的信息以及论述，这些介绍将不会过于繁琐、深究。

